## Install the .NET SDK:
The .NET Software Development Kit (SDK) is the core component. 
It contains everything required to build and run .NET applications, including the ASP.NET Core framework and the .NET Command Line Interface (CLI).

Download the latest Long Term Support (LTS) or Standard Term Support (STS) version of the .NET SDK from the official Microsoft .NET website. 
Installing the SDK automatically installs the necessary runtimes and the ASP.NET Core components.

## Choose and Install an IDE(Visual Studio 2022 Community edition):
IDE stands for Integrated Development Environment ðŸ’».
Visual Studio (Recommended for Windows): 
Download and install the latest version of Visual Studio (e.g., Visual Studio 2022 Community edition is free for individuals). 
During installation, ensure you select the "ASP.NET and web development" workload to get all the templates and tools for MVC development.









